<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="xfce-allow-panel-customization" role="function"/>xfce_allow_panel_customization ()</title>
<indexterm><primary>xfce_allow_panel_customization</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>            xfce_allow_panel_customization      (void);</programlisting>
<para>
Check if the user is allowed to customize the panel. Uses the kiosk mode
implementation from libxfce4util.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> <link linkend="TRUE:CAPS"><literal>TRUE</literal></link> if the user is allowed to customize the panel, <link linkend="FALSE:CAPS"><literal>FALSE</literal></link>
         otherwise.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
